<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p>Fragment from the lower edge of a <rs type="objectType">sarcophagus</rs>, with right edge apparently surviving (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.42</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.14</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.37</measure>).</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> on the face.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p>Standard forms; <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.017</measure></p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p><date notBefore="0101" notAfter="0300" exact="none">Second to third centuries A.D.</date> (<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>).</p>
</div>
<div type="edition" lang="grc">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
<ab><lb n="1"/>  <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character" dim="left"/>  <w lemma="ἀσεβής"><supplied reason="lost">ἀσεβ</supplied><unclear reason="damage">ὴ</unclear>ς</w> <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w> <w lemma="ἐπάρατος">ἐπάρατο<supplied reason="lost">ς</supplied></w>  <lb n="2"/><w lemma="καί"><supplied reason="lost">και</supplied></w> <w lemma="τυμβωρύχος"><supplied reason="lost">τυμβωρύχοι</supplied></w> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character" dim="left"/><orig n="unresolved">οσιοις</orig>     <space extent="4" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  </ab>
</div>

<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character" dim="left"/> sacrilegious and  accursed <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character" dim="right"/> and grave-robbers <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character" dim="right"/></p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>l. 1 is from the funerary curse upon those who disturb the tomb; l. 2 is not from any of the standard formulae. Could there be a use of <foreign lang="grc">ἀνόσιοι</foreign> to those cursed?</p>
</div>
